{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"archaic-elegant-bovine","description":"## Why\n`docs/concurrency.md:249-257` explicitly records a historical data-loss mode — a tracker\ndetached at a local commit while `refs/heads/tickets` lags behind it, where a branch-ref\ncomparison could conclude \"no local work\" and `reset --hard` away the unpushed commit —\nand states there is **no dedicated automated regression test** after the historical shell\ntest was retired in the bash to Python migration. The current guard lives at\n`src/rebar/_store/sync.py:94-98` (`rev-list {remote}..HEAD`, ff-adopt only when local is\nnot ahead). VALIDATED: the successor test is genuinely absent.\n\n## What\nAdd an integration test that pins the WS3 fix behaviorally.\n\n## Scope\n- Test only (`tests/unit/` or `tests/integration/` alongside `test_sync_union_recovery.py`).\n- Build origin + tracker; detach tracker HEAD; create a local-only commit that advances\n  HEAD but not `refs/heads/tickets`; advance `origin/tickets`; run read-side reconvergence.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Test named e.g. `test_sync_preserves_detached_head_local_ahead_commit`.\n- [ ] Asserts both the local event and the remote event are reachable and replayed after\n      reconvergence.\n- [ ] Asserts no `reset`/gc can orphan the local commit (commit stays reachable).\n- [ ] `make test` green.","id":"b6c5-3461-a6da-4eda","parent_id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","priority":1,"tags":["p0","sync","data-safety"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Add detached-HEAD local-ahead sync preservation regression test"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784805671942001,"uuid":"0907c71b-f443-4ef0-be6b-dc4122b5343f"}